review_blob: Bottle. It poured an orange gold color with a white head. The aroma was floral, citrus and malt with grapefruit, orange and caramel flavors. Very nice.

Bottle: Amber in color with a white head and lacing. The aroma was malt and some hoppy floral notes, while it had a caramel and slightly fruity finish. It was full body with some mild bitterness on the finish.
Bottle: It poured a hazy orange gold with a white head. It had a slight wheat aroma with a minimally tart taste. I found it just average.

Draft. Ruby red with a frothy biege head. Slight fruit aroma. It has a fair amount of hoppy (citrus) and caramel flavors with a medium bitterness level.
5.2% abv
beer_name: Old Black Bear Whooping Crane Red Ale

review_blob: Draft. Amber in color with a thin off-white head. Not much on the aroma. The taste is sour / pickle veggies.
Bottle: It poured a clear gold. It had a light floral nose with a sweet malty caramel taste. Very smooth and well balanced.
Bottle. Golden color. Some fruit esters and some spices up front with a malt finish.
Bottle. Orange in color with a white head. Hoppy aroma. Tropical fruit flavor. Moderate bitterness.
Bottle. Orange gold in color. Aroma is malt, floral and some citrus. Very nice back porch IPA.
Bottle. A dark straw golden color with a white head. Hoppy citrus notes with a moderate bitterness level.
Bottle. Semi-opaque red color with an off-white head. Flavor is citrus and caramel. It is moderately bitter.
Bottle. Golden color with a white head. It had a floral aroma and hoppy taste. The bitterness is moderate.
Draft. It poured a clear orange golden color with a thin white head. The aroma and flavor is sweet mango. The taste has both sweet and heat from the peppers. Almost too sweet.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series # 7: Mango Magnifico con Calor

review_blob: Draft. Dark ruby red in color with an off-white lace ring. The aroma is dark stone fruits. Very sour.
Draft. Clear gold in color, poured with a small white head. Spiced aroma and flavor. Lasting aftertaste.
Bottle. Clear gold in color with a thin white head. The hoppy aroma was tropical with a sweet undertone in the taste.

Draft in Growler. It poured an amber color with a thin white head and minimal lacing. The aroma was light floral hops. The taste was tropical fruit and some caramel malt. I kept the beer overnight in the growler so I will try this one again.
Bottle. Amber color with a big frothy biege head. The aroma and flavoring includes orange, coriander, and Belgium yeast esters. Very tasty.

Bottle: Cloudy orange gold in color with a white head that maintains a thin covering and lace ring. It has a nice hoppy aroma and taste. 
An easy drinking ale.
Bottle: Poured an amber color with a thin white head. Light citrus aroma with flavors of grapefruit, pine and some caramel on the end. It has a slight bitterness on the finish.
Bottle: It poured gold with a thin white head. The aroma was citrus with a tart pink grapefruit taste.
Bottle. It pour pale gold with no head at all. The aroma was faint ginger. The flavor and taste was ginger, medicinal, and sweet. Overall, a disappointment.
beer_name: Small Town Not Your Fathers Ginger Ale

review_blob: Draft. It poured a clear reddish gold with a white head and lacing. Slight fruity aroma with an intense hoppy taste - citrus and pine. The watermelon comes through on the back end.
beer_name: Ballast Point Dorado Double IPA - Watermelon

review_blob: Draft. Black in color with a beige head. The aroma is roasted malt and the flavor is dark chocolate and coffee. It was well balanced with a smooth finish. Enjoyable.
beer_name: Old Black Bear Black Bears Delight Coffee Stout

review_blob: Draft. Poured black with beige head and lacing. Aroma is roasted malt. The flavor is coffee and dark chocolate. It is well balanced with a very smooth finish.
Draft. Pale golden in color and poured with a thin White head. Not much on the aroma while the taste is hoppy with a little citrus in the back end. Slightly bitter. Very nice.
beer_name: Old Black Bear 256 Extra Pale Ale

review_blob: Draft. Murky brown with a beige head and lacing. Aroma and flavor is roasted malt and nuts. Very smooth and easy to drink. A very nice first introduction to this new Alabama brewery.
Draft. Dark burgundy in color with off-white head. Caramel malt aroma. Some dark fruitiness in the aftertaste.
Bottle. It poured a golden orange color with a white head. The aroma was faint. The flavors include pine and some citrus with a mostly resinous bitter finish.
Draft. Clear ruby red with an off-white head. Bitter dark fruit taste. The addition of blood orange really changes the Brother Joseph profile.
beer_name: Straight To Ale Blood Orange Brother Josephs

review_blob: Draft. Cloudy straw gold in color with a white head and lacing. Light aroma with earthy, herbal and grass notes. It has a lingering slightly bitter aftertaste.
12 oz can. It poured a cloudy golden color with a white head and lacing. Hoppy citrus and pine aroma. Taste is moderately bitter with a slightly dry finish.

Bottle: Murky brown with a off-white head and lace. The aroma is caramel malt and spiciness. The flavors included spices, caramel, plum and raisins. It was well balanced with a strong sense of alcohol at the end.

Can. Black in color with a big frothy tan head that settled into about 1/2 inch covering. The aroma is milk chocolate and roasted malt. The flavor is black coffee, chocolate and some vague dark fruit notes. The taste is sweet with a hint of saltiness, while its medium body is thick and creamy. The best of the Nitro Project offerings.

Can: It poured like a off-white smoothie before settling into a clear copper color with a thick off-white head. The aroma is floral and the flavor is the same with an off-taste resin undertone. It has a strongly bitter finish as well. Overall, just a fair IPA.
Bottle. Cloudy gold in color with a nice white head that is well maintained by the active carbonation. The aroma and flavor include clove, bread, and fruity citrus. Very nice.
Draft. Clear ruby red with a biege head and lacing. Tropical fruit aroma. Medium bitterness. Very nice.
Draft. Hazy gold with a frothy white head. Light aroma with stale bread taste. Not what I was expecting.
Draft. Dark red in color with a white head. Slight cherry aroma, but stronger flavoring. Mellow taste with a slightly sweet finish.
Draft. Clear straw golden color with a quickly dissipating white head and lacing. Floral and grass aroma. Mild bitterness.

Draft at the brewery. Amber in color. 
This sour version of Rocket City Red has a funky aroma that is dominated by the sour taste.

Draft. Amber color with a one finger white head that quickly dissipated. 
It had a light fruity aroma with dark fruit flavors and spiciness.
Draft. Gold color with frothy white head. Aroma of floral and pine. Mild bitterness.
Bottle. Pale gold in color with a white head. Mild citrus aroma with flavors of prickly pear and grapefruit. The taste is tart with a light bodied mouth feel.

Bottle in a shaker glass. It poured a clear golden color with a white head . The aroma was floral and citrus/lemon. The flavor tropical fruit and pine. It has a low level of bitterness on the front end.
Bottle. Poured copper with a white head. Flavors is wheat and clove. Very drinkable.
Draft at brewery. Dark red with a thin head. Aroma of dark chocolate. The flavor is chocolate, coffee and raspberries. Desert in a glass. Very sweet.
Draft. Golden in color. Tropical fruity aroma. Sweet malty flavoring. The alcohol kicks in at the end.
beer_name: Straight To Ale Church Street Tripel

review_blob: Draft at brewery. Amber color. Malty aroma with some fruity and bread dough flavors.
Draft. Black with tan head and light lacing. Roasted malt aroma and flavors. It is well balanced.
